        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 25 at 5:17PM MDT until June 25 at 6:15PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>SVRBIS

The National Weather Service in Bismarck has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Bowman County in southwestern North Dakota...

* Until 615 PM MDT.

* At 517 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 18 miles west of
Mud Buttes, or 21 miles northeast of Ekalaka, moving southeast at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Bowman County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
